<dl id="n30100j"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n30" href="#n30100j">N30 (VI.B.22)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n30all.htm#n30100j"> 100(j)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Mecca <font color="red"><sup><teeny>|a</teeny></sup></font>rotten with vice<font color="red"><sup><teeny>a|</teeny></sup></font> Chicago / Const <font color="green">[Stanti]</font> / Pekin</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The World&apos;s / Worst City / Distinction Sought / by Many When &ldquo;Sacred&rdquo; / Means &ldquo;Sordid&rdquo;. / (by Bryon Bellingham). Which is the worst city in the World? There are many that may be reagrded as candidates for this unenviable distinction, and, happily, none is within the British Empire. &hellip; <mark>Chicago</mark> &hellip; far-off days when W.T. Stead startled the English-speaking world with his terrible exposure, and dared to foresee what might happen &ldquo;if Christ came to Chicago&rdquo; &hellip; Moscow &hellip; <mark>Peking</mark> &hellip; City of Mexico &hellip; Jerusalem &hellip; <mark>Mecca is rotten with vice</mark> and corruption &hellip; <mark>Constantinople</mark> is in rapid decline, not only because the power of the Turk has waned, but because persons and property are help cheap. <small> <a name="IT1jun28" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#IT1jun28"><cite title="source">Irish Times</cite></a> (1 June 1928) 4</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
